South African farmers are growing 'swazi gold' in the tiny state of Swaziland . 
  The plant is a potent strain of cannabis that stays in the country and is used to make heroin . 
  Youngsters as young as 14 are mixing swazi gold with heroin to form nyope . 
  BBC Stacey Dooley Investigates reveals how the drug is ruining lives . 
 